Attempted murder arrest after Coventry petrol station attack
A 41-year-old man has been arrested on suspicion of attempted murder following an attack at a petrol station forecourt.Police were called to a petrol station on Binley Road in Stoke, Coventry, at around 06:00 GMT following reports of a "disturbance on the forecourt".A 36-year-old man was seriously assaulted and remains in a critical condition, West Midlands Police said.Both men are believed to have known each other.Det Sgt Joel Mildinhall said: "Officers attended and found the local man with serious head injuries."The motive for the attack and its precise location remain unclear, police said.A forensic investigation is underway and the victim's Audi A4 car, which was at the petrol station, has been taken away for analysis.